<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Space Management on Saitech</title><link>https://saitech.blog/tags/space-management/</link><description>Recent content in Space Management on Saitech</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 21 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://saitech.blog/tags/space-management/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Quick Tools to Manage Space Usage</title><link>https://saitech.blog/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/</link><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saitech.blog/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://saitech.blog/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/1.png" alt="Featured image of post Quick Tools to Manage Space Usage" /&gt;&lt;p&gt;From time to time, you might need to free up disk space, but where do you start? How can you quickly locate those large files taking up valuable storage? Letâ€™s explore some options. Spoiler alert: The first two are my top picks!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="terminal"&gt;Terminal
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Command to Locate Large Files&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
&lt;table class="lntable"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;find / -type f -size +2000M 2&amp;gt;/dev/null
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;/&lt;/code&gt;: Search from the root directory (change to specific directories like /home or /var for faster results).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;-type f&lt;/code&gt;: Search for files only.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;-size +2000M&lt;/code&gt;: Files larger than 2000 MB.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;2&amp;gt;/dev/null&lt;/code&gt;: Suppress permission denied errors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://saitech.blog/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/2.png"
width="917"
height="91"
srcset="https://saitech.blog/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/2_hu_265e8a25a28c8d98.png 480w, https://saitech.blog/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/2_hu_8b5ab8f484028146.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="find / -type f"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="1007"
data-flex-basis="2418px"
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="ncdu"&gt;Ncdu
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Install ncdu:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
&lt;table class="lntable"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;sudo pacman -S ncdu
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Run ncdu:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
&lt;table class="lntable"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;ncdu /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Use arrow keys to navigate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://saitech.blog/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/1.png"
width="850"
height="428"
srcset="https://saitech.blog/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/1_hu_cc3afc7aff852d76.png 480w, https://saitech.blog/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/1_hu_78d099765d46c35c.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="ncdu"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="198"
data-flex-basis="476px"
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="gui-tool"&gt;GUI tool
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you prefer graphical tools, you can use baobab:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
&lt;table class="lntable"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;sudo pacman -S baobab
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://saitech.blog/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/3.png"
width="958"
